HEADWORD: Rout cake
<hw>Rout" cake`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A kind of rich sweet cake made
for routs, or evening parties.</def></p>

<p><q>Twenty-four little <qex>rout cakes</qex> that were lying neglected
in a plate.</q> <rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

